 `FieldDecoder`s are automatically generated by the `graphqelm` CLI command.
You can use `Graphqelm.FieldDecoder.map` to transform a value.
@docs map, FieldDecoder

 `Graphqelm.Encode.Value`s are usually low-level details used by generated code.
Currently users need to pass Encode Values in for InputObject arguments, but
otherwise they are only used by the code generated by the `graphqelm` CLI tool.

@docs null, bool, enum, int, list, string, object, maybe
